### FINDING: X-Content-Type-Options Header Missing
SEVERITY: Low
EVIDENCE: `"alert": "X-Content-Type-Options Header Missing"`, `"url": "http://192.168.1.49:4280/robots.txt"`, `"description": "The Anti-MIME-Sniffing header X-Content-Type-Options was not set to 'nosniff'."`
REASONING: The server does not send the `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` header. This allows older browsers (and some modern ones in specific modes) to "sniff" the MIME type of the response, potentially executing a downloaded script as HTML or vice versa.
EXPLOITABILITY: Moderate — Requires the attacker to host a malicious file or manipulate the response to trick the browser.
IMPACT: Potential for MIME-type confusion attacks, leading to the execution of malicious scripts or the display of sensitive data in an unintended context.
REMEDIATION: Configure the web server to send `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` for all responses.
